('chunk_6f882cdd206375b32c','file_162fce15bbe62004d5','geography.md','I&S Related Concepts (used throughout the year)','- **Causality** (cause and effect) — why biomes, poverty or scarcity occur.
- **Processes** — soil formation, nutrient cycling, the water cycle, development.
- **Sustainability** — meeting present needs without harming the future.
- **Resources** — natural, human and man-made means of meeting needs.
- **Disparity / equity** — the North–South divide, inequality, uneven development.
- **Perspective** — different stakeholders view resource use and development differently.
- **Globalization, power, culture, cooperation** — supporting concepts used in Units 2–3.','{"related":1,"concepts":2,"used":2,"throughout":1,"the":4,"year":1,"causality":1,"cause":1,"and":3,"effect":1,"why":1,"biomes":1,"poverty":1,"scarcity":1,"occur":1,"processes":1,"soil":1,"formation":1,"nutrient":1,"cycling":1,"water":1,"cycle":1,"development":3,"sustainability":1,"meeting":2,"present":1,"needs":2,"without":1,"harming":1,"future":1,"resources":1,"natural":1,"human":1,"man":1,"made":1,"means":1,"disparity":1,"equity":1,"north":1,"south":1,"divide":1,"inequality":1,"uneven":1,"perspective":1,"different":1,"stakeholders":1,"view":1,"resource":1,"use":1,"differently":1,"globalization":1,"power":1,"culture":1,"cooperation":1,"supporting":1,"units":1}'::jsonb),
